# Cursor Rules ‚Äî Ametyst Landing Page

## Project overview
Marketing landing page for Ametyst, a banking platform for autonomous AI agents.
Next.js 15 (App Router) ¬∑ TypeScript 5 ¬∑ Tailwind CSS 3 ¬∑ React 19 ¬∑ Deployed on Vercel.

---

## Language & runtime
- **TypeScript** everywhere ‚Äî no `.js` files except config files that require it (`next.config.js`, `postcss.config.js`)
- **React 19** with the App Router ‚Äî use Server Components by default; add `"use client"` only when you need browser APIs, event handlers, or `useState`/`useEffect`
- **Node.js 18+** required for local development
- **npm** is the package manager ‚Äî do not use yarn, pnpm, or bun

---

## Project structure
```
app/            Next.js App Router (layouts, pages, API routes)
components/     React UI section components (flat, PascalCase)
contexts/       React context providers (empty, add only if needed)
hooks/          Custom React hooks (empty, add only if needed)
public/         Static assets served at /
docs/           Project documentation (do not modify unless updating docs)
```

---

## TypeScript rules
- Always type component props explicitly ‚Äî no implicit `any`
- Prefer `interface` over `type` for object shapes; use `type` for unions and primitives
- Use plain function declarations with typed props ‚Äî avoid `React.FC`
- API route handlers must type the `Request` parameter and return `NextResponse`
- Do not use `@ts-ignore` or `@ts-expect-error` without a comment explaining why
- TypeScript strict mode is enabled (`tsconfig.json`) ‚Äî do not relax strict settings

---

## Styling
- **Tailwind CSS only** ‚Äî no CSS modules, no styled-components, no inline `style` objects except where Tailwind cannot express the value (e.g. dynamic values not available as a class)
- **Semantic color aliases** ‚Äî always use the Tailwind aliases, never raw hex in class names:
  - `bg-bg` / `text-fg` ‚Äî background and primary text
  - `text-muted` ‚Äî secondary/muted text
  - `border-border` ‚Äî borders and dividers
  - `bg-btn-bg` / `text-btn-fg` / `border-btn-border` ‚Äî button colors
- **Font families**:
  - `font-headline` ‚Äî Neue Machina (headings, brand name)
  - `font-body` ‚Äî Inter (body text, UI labels)
- **Light mode only** ‚Äî do not add `dark:` variants; the site is light-mode by design
- Color tokens are CSS custom properties defined in `app/globals.css`; to change a brand color, edit the `--color-*` variables there ‚Äî do not change the Tailwind alias names in `tailwind.config.ts`

---

## Component conventions
- One component per file, filename matches the component name (PascalCase: `Hero.tsx`)
- All landing page sections live in `components/` ‚Äî never inline section markup in `app/page.tsx`
- Every section component must have a root element with `id="<section-name>"` for anchor-based navigation
- Client components (`"use client"`) go in `components/`; keep `app/page.tsx` and `app/layout.tsx` as Server Components
- Do not create sub-folders inside `components/` unless a section grows to multiple files

---

## Routing (App Router)
- Page files: `app/<route>/page.tsx`
- Layout files: `app/<route>/layout.tsx` ‚Äî only if the route needs its own layout
- API routes: `app/api/<endpoint>/route.ts` ‚Äî export named HTTP method handlers (`GET`, `POST`, etc.)
- Use `export const metadata` in `layout.tsx` or `page.tsx` for SEO metadata ‚Äî never use `<Head>` from `next/head`

---

## API routes
- Always validate inputs server-side before processing
- Return `NextResponse.json(...)` with appropriate HTTP status codes
- Never expose environment variables or secrets in response bodies
- Use `cache: "no-store"` on any `fetch` calls inside API routes that must not be cached
- The waitlist route (`app/api/waitlist/route.ts`) is the reference implementation for input validation and error handling

---

## Environment variables
- Secret variables live in `.env.local` (gitignored) ‚Äî never commit this file
- The only required secret is `GOOGLE_SCRIPT_URL` (used by the waitlist API)
- Access env vars server-side only ‚Äî never import `process.env.*` inside client components
- Document any new env var in `docs/ECOSYSTEM.md`

---

## Linting & formatting
- Run `npm run lint` (`next lint`) before committing ‚Äî fix all ESLint errors; do not disable rules inline without justification
- No Prettier config is present; follow the existing code style: 2-space indent, double quotes in JSX attributes, no trailing commas in function arguments
- Do not add `console.log` calls in production code ‚Äî remove before committing
- Do not add `eslint-disable` comments without a brief explanation of why

---

## Build & deployment
- Build command: `npm run build` ‚Äî must produce zero TypeScript errors and zero ESLint errors
- Dev server: `npm run dev`
- `next.config.js` uses `output: 'standalone'` ‚Äî required for Vercel/Docker; do not change
- The `.next/` and `node_modules/` folders are gitignored; never commit build artifacts
- Deployment target: Vercel (auto-detects Next.js, no extra config needed)

---

## What NOT to do
- ‚ùå No `any` types without explicit justification
- ‚ùå No hardcoded hex color values in component JSX ‚Äî use Tailwind aliases
- ‚ùå No `dark:` Tailwind variants ‚Äî light mode only
- ‚ùå No markup directly in `app/page.tsx` ‚Äî extract to a component in `components/`
- ‚ùå No removal of the honeypot field in `Waitlist.tsx`
- ‚ùå No changes to `output: 'standalone'` in `next.config.js`
- ‚ùå No committing `.env*.local` or any credentials
- ‚ùå No `console.log` left in production code
- ‚ùå No `eslint-disable` comments without explaining the reason
- ‚ùå No yarn / pnpm / bun ‚Äî use npm only
